AZAM FC have secured the signing of Nigerian attacking midfielder Isah Ndala on a two-year deal. Ndala, who was until recently a midfielder with former league champions, Plateau United, has signed a contract in front of the team’s owner, Yusuf Bakhresa, and Chief Executive Officer, Abdulkarim Amin ‘Popat’.   Calabar Port roars back to life after three years of…     Drogba: Osimhen can be ‘best striker in the…     Remo Stars Ewelike’s season over   The midfielder, who has a great shape, and a reputation for aggression and passing, is coming to strengthen the midfield area, where in September this year he will be turning 20 years old. In addition to playing for Plateau, Ndala has also joined the Nasarawa United team where he started competitive football in 2018, before landing in Plateau United in 2020. He was loaned out to Armenia’s topflight side, Sevan FC at the beginning of last season but returned to the club thNeal’sar. Ndala becomes Azam FC third signing for next season, after the switch of two stars from Ivory Coast, Kipre Junior, and Tape Edinho to the club.